# SWIM Documentation Index

Quick reference guide for navigating the SWIM domain knowledge and implementation rules.

## Documentation Files

### Core SWIM Knowledge

#### 1. swim-domain-knowledge.mdc
**Core SWIM concepts and aviation information management**

Topics: SWIM overview, SWIM-TI Yellow Profile, message patterns (pub/sub), protocols (AMQP 1.0, HTTP/REST), security (EACP, mTLS, SASL), data models (AIXM, FIXM, DNOTAM), Subscription Manager, infrastructure requirements, glossary

**Start here** to understand SWIM fundamentals.

#### 2. swim-dnotam-ed254.mdc ⭐ UPDATED
**DNOTAM (Digital NOTAM) service specification**

Topics: DNOTAM Service Definition (SWIM Registry), Yellow Profile protocol requirements, Current vs Digital NOTAM, supported event types (runway closure, taxiway closure, stand status, obstacle, navaid, airspace), mandatory use cases (ePIB, take-off/landing, runway contamination), CP1 requirements, AIFS/AMAP integration, compliance checklist

**Important**: DNOTAM uses SWIM Registry Service Definition + Yellow Profile (SPEC-170). **ED-254 is for AMAN only, NOT for DNOTAM**.

#### 3. swim-sesar-cp1.mdc ⭐ NEW
**SESAR Common Project 1 regulatory framework and requirements**

Topics: EU Regulation 116/2021, Single European Sky, EASA rulemaking, AF5 deployment families, SWIM PKI and cyber security, AIM services (AIFS, AMAP, DNOTAM), stakeholder roles (AISP, ANSP, AO, EAD), 18 CP1 airports, 2026 deadline, compliance assessment

**Essential for understanding regulatory context**.

#### 4. swim-cp1-services.mdc ⭐ NEW
**Complete catalog of CP1 SWIM services beyond core AIM**

Topics: Meteorological Information Exchange (IWXXM, METAR, TAF, SIGMET), SADIS (World Area Forecast System), MET3SG, Extended AMAN, FF-ICE, service registry, data formats, integration patterns, future enhancements

**Reference for all CP1 services**.

